  <summary date="2012-02-24T23:06:49Z" status="Introduced in House">Health Freedom for Seniors Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow tax-free transfers of required distributions after age 70 1/2 from an individual retirement account (IRA) and other tax-exempt retirement accounts to a health savings account.&#160; Exempts such transfers from the excise tax on excess contributions to tax-favored accounts and annuities.</summary>
